Are you hurt?

87
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:44,490
Do you need someone to help you?

88
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:46,270
Do you believe in angels?

89
00:03:46,270 --> 00:03:48,020
Yes, I do.

90
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:49,620
I do believe in angels, Jacob.

91
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:57,140
Jacob needs an angel
right now, real bad.

92
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:58,630
BART: Jacob.

93
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:01,120
Jacob, get over here now.

94
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,340
I hear someone else with you.

95
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:04,160
Is it someone you know, Jacob.

96
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,430
Are you at home?

97
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:06,930
Do you know your address?

98
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:09,920
Can you tell me where you are?

99
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:10,920
Bart.

100
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,420
Please let me talk to him.

101
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:14,910
Jacob, get out here now.

102
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:16,910
Jacob, where are you?

103
00:04:16,910 --> 00:04:21,400
[WHIMPERING]

104
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:26,390
[MUSIC PLAYING]

105
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:39,860
[WHIMPERING]

106
00:04:42,850 --> 00:04:45,350
Jacob.

107
00:04:45,350 --> 00:04:47,350
Daddy, please, no.

108
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:48,340
Please.

109
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:49,340
HOTLINE: Jacob?

110
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:50,340
BART: Come on.

111
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:51,340
Jacob?

112
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:52,890
Jake?

113
00:04:52,890 --> 00:04:53,670
Got a phone number.

114
00:04:53,670 --> 00:04:55,060
And it's local.

115
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:57,830
[SIRENS]

116
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,660
Our son makes prank
calls all the time.

117
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:00,540
Tell them, honey.

118
00:05:00,540 --> 00:05:01,240
That's right.

119
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,240
He's only nine.

120
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,160
You know how children can be.

121
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,420
There's no problem
here, officers.

122
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:08,040
I understand
that, Mr. Fletcher.

123
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,360
We still need to speak with him.

124
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,390
He went out with friends.

125
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:13,220
At this hour?

126
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:14,050
The boy's nine, you said.

127
00:05:22,230 --> 00:05:23,670
It's all right.

128
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:26,090
You'll be OK.

129
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:28,350
OFFICER: We found him
beaten, tied to his bed.

130
00:05:28,350 --> 00:05:29,420
There were marks on the posts.

131
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,680
So this wasn't the first time.

132
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,400
Kid hasn't said a
word since then.

133
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,670
You left him with
our doctor, right?

134
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:34,370
Yes, ma'am.

135
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:36,030
He's in the exam room now.

136
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:37,350
Get the paperwork started.

137
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:38,620
I'll get to the scene.

138
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:39,690
Thank you.

139
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:42,790
How did Jacob ever find the
strength to make that call?

140
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:44,010
It's a miracle.

141
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,520
We've seen our share
of those over the years.

142
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,550
Remember Tokyo?

143
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:50,870
Our first miracle.

144
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:53,510
[SINGING]

145
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:23,940
So are you boys
having a great time

146
00:06:23,940 --> 00:06:25,910
Over here on this
side of the Pacific?

147
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:28,860
[BOOS]

148
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:30,830
We heard you might
need some new recruits.

149
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:33,430
Think you could squeeze us in?

150
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:37,680
[CHEERING]

151
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,000
Well, in that
case, Private Sara.

152
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,790
And Private Yvonne
reporting for duty.

153
00:06:41,790 --> 00:06:46,250
[CHEERING]

154
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:48,190
Could one of you boys
point me in the direction

155
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:50,840
Of the Air Force
beautiful parlor?

156
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,330
You don't need one.

157
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,820
Oh, aren't you boys so sweet.

158
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,810
Why can't the boys
at home be like you?

159
00:06:56,810 --> 00:06:59,300
Move over here.

160
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:03,290
[CHEERING]

161
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:09,260
[SINGING]

162
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:10,060
[SIRENS]

163
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:10,760
Sorry.

164
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,750
Sorry, ladies.

165
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:13,740
We've got to cut
this short, ladies.

166
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:14,540
Are we under attack?

167
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:15,240
It's another siren.

168
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,570
We've got to get you
back to your hotel.

169
00:07:16,570 --> 00:07:17,530
Come on.

170
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:18,230
Careful.

171
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:20,220
Let's go.

172
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:24,700
[BACKGROUND VOICES]

173
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:25,700
Welcome to typhoon season.

174
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:28,190
October in Japan.

175
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:30,680
How long do these storms last?

176
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,170
Anybody's guess.

177
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:33,660
But we have more shows.

178
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:35,660
They're expecting us in Korea.

179
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:36,750
We can't fight an act of God.

180
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:41,000
He maybe wants you to stay here.

181
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,990
[CAR SCREECHING]

182
00:07:41,990 --> 00:07:44,470
Oh.

183
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:45,470
Sit tight.

184
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:46,460
I'll be right back.

185
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,690
Oh, Sara, look.

186
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:05,900
Oh, my goodness.

187
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,880
What are they doing out there?

188
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,270
You shouldn't be
dressed like that.

189
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:21,250
You'll catch your death.

190
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,230
Why aren't you guys at home?

191
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:25,990
You understand
home, your parents?

192
00:08:25,990 --> 00:08:26,690
Mama-sahn.

193
00:08:26,690 --> 00:08:27,390
Papa-sahn.

194
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:31,640
Oh, my lord.

195
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,630
Think they're orphans?

196
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:36,900
Are you hungry?

197
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:39,330
I have some candy in my pockets.

198
00:08:39,330 --> 00:08:40,960
Oh, my goodness.

199
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,660
OK.

200
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:44,060
Bet they haven't had
a decent meal in days.

201
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:47,800
Come on, kids.

202
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,500
Come, come, come.

203
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,200
What are you doing?

204
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,470
We can't leave
them out her, Sara.

205
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:51,170
They'll freeze.

206
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:51,950
Come on, honeys.

207
00:08:51,950 --> 00:08:52,940
Come on.

208
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,400
This is going to
lead to trouble.

209
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,180
Come on.

210
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:56,880
Come on.

211
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:57,870
OK, that's it.

212
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,850
Let's go.

213
00:08:58,850 --> 00:09:00,130
OK, come on.

214
00:09:00,130 --> 00:09:00,830
Come on.

215
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:03,780
Let's go get dry.

216
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:04,560
Here we go.

217
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:05,260
Here we go.

218
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:05,960
Open the door.

219
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,740
That's it.

220
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:19,200
Spot's our mascot.

221
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:23,900
He won't let anything
bad happen to you.

222
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,570
My name is Dr. Riggs.

223
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:28,010
And I'm only here to
make sure you're OK.

224
00:09:28,010 --> 00:09:30,430
Are you good with that?

225
00:09:30,430 --> 00:09:31,130
OK.

226
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:38,560
Let's just have a look here.

227
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:43,270
This must have hurt.

228
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:50,600
You want to tell me about it?

229
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:54,710
Is it OK if I take a picture?

230
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:17,290
I thought you'd want
to see these, Detective.

231
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:18,630
These Polaroids
were in their room?

232
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:31,160
[POLICE RADIO]

233
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,330
Anything you might have seen?

234
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:33,840
Anything at all
could be helpful.

235
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:37,170
People in this neighborhood
keep to themselves, Detective.

236
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:41,430
Privacy is very important to us.

237
00:10:41,430 --> 00:10:43,210
More important than
protecting a child?

238
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,920
That boy still needs your help.

239
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:48,980
Give it some thought.

240
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,510
Call me if anything
comes to mind.

241
00:10:56,240 --> 00:11:00,160
I've seen your x-rays, Jacob.

242
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:03,180
You have some broken bones
that didn't heal very well.

243
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:06,340
Did you know that?

244
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:07,760
Can you tell me
how that happened?

245
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,480
Take your time.

246
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:16,530
There's no hurry.

247
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:26,390
The boy's still not talking.

248
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:28,990
Not a word so far.

249
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:30,200
Well, he called our hotline.

250
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,920
And he spoke to one
of the counselors.

251
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,920
So we knew he can talk.

252
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:37,220
Just from observation earlier,
he's about two years behind.

253
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,830
He can't read very well.

254
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:42,490
Typical for abused children.

255
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:45,730
His father's a
big shot attorney.

256
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:49,360
No police record
for him or his wife.

257
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:53,610
But Jacob's teacher did
file a report last month.

258
00:11:53,610 --> 00:11:57,100
Too many sick days,
suspicious injuries.

259
00:11:57,100 --> 00:12:01,090
Parents actually
documented their abuse.

260
00:12:01,090 --> 00:12:01,890
What do you mean?

261
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,590
Polaroids.

262
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:07,920
Mrs. Fletcher's admitted
showing them to Jacob

263
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:09,960
And promising it
would all happen again

264
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,890
If he didn't do
what they told him.

265
00:12:11,890 --> 00:12:13,020
No wonder the
boy's not talking.

266
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,410
He's terrified.

267
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:16,110
I've seen that in
private practice before.

268
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:18,290
But Polaroids?

269
00:12:18,290 --> 00:12:20,830
Is there a spot for Jacob
at the Merv Griffin Village?

270
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:22,270
Wickenburg is at capacity.

271
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:24,470
And so is our Virginia facility.

272
00:12:24,470 --> 00:12:26,500
What about
California, Beaumont?

273
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:27,880
Yvonne is already
working on that.

274
00:12:31,740 --> 00:12:36,070
What's he holding back?

275
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:37,650
It's a secret, children.

276
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:38,690
No one should know you're here.

277
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,210
Uh, just a minute.

278
00:12:43,210 --> 00:12:43,910
Aloha.

279
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:49,840
